Interface BaseStreamDecorator<T,S extends BaseStream<T,S>>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the elements of the stream
    S - the type of the stream
    All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable, BaseStream<T,S>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    DoubleStreamDecorator, IntStreamDecorator, LongStreamDecorator, StreamDecorator<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ResourceStream, ResourceStream.DoubleResourceStream, ResourceStream.IntResourceStream, ResourceStream.LongResourceStream, ResourceStream.ReferenceResourceStream

    public interface BaseStreamDecorator<T,S extends BaseStream<T,S>>
extends BaseStream<T,S>
    A decorator for a BaseStream which wraps intermediate and terminal operations such that they can be easily extended.

    Intermediate operations will return a wrapper over the result of applying that operation to the component, such that raw references to component streams cannot escape their wrapping.
